The paper proposes a novel embedding method for Named Entity Disambiguation (NED), which is a task related to natural language processing (NLP) and information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as the skip-gram model and KB graph model, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) research, suggesting cs.AI as another likely sub-category. The paper also involves vector space modeling, which is a common technique in machine learning and data mining, suggesting cs.LG (Learning) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with knowledge bases, which are often used in database (DB) research, suggesting cs.DB as a less likely but still possible sub-category.
